description:
Alfred Hitchcock's MEMORY OF THE CAMPS (DVD5)

War-Propaganda Runtime: 60 minutes

Warning: extremely graphic scenes, thousands of corpses.

 &quot; We shall never know who they were...whether they were Catholics, Lutherans, or Jews...and so they lie, Jew, Lutherans and Catholics, indistinguishable, cheek to cheek, in a common grave...African Negroes, Albanians, Austrians, Belgians, Brazilians, Bulgarians, Canadians, Chinese, Croats, Czechs, Danes, French, Germans, British, Greeks, Dutch, Italians, Yugoslavs, Latvians, Norwegians, Mexicans, Poles, Romanians, Spaniards, Swiss, Americans and Russians..&quot;

When Allied troops invaded Germany and liberated the camps at the end of World War II, they found unspeakable horrors that still haunt the world's conscience. In 1945, British and American film crews, accompanying the troops liberating the camps captured these atrocities firsthand. 

The resulting film, directed in part by Alfred Hitchcock, but never finished, was discovered by FRONTLINE in 1984, in the archives of the Imperial War Museum. Sixty years after the war ended, FRONTLINE now re-broadcasts this powerful memorial in it's entirety. Have you ever seen a swimming-pool sized trough full of corpses? Now here's your big chance.

There were more than 200 children under 12 years-old found still alive in Belsen camp...some had been born there -- just like in Gaza, except for there's 800,000 children under siege by zionists there, in something of a Warsaw ghetto, with the most restrictive land, sea and air blockade in place. Almost 800 Gazan tunnels to Egypt (80%) have been destroyed to this date (in 2013 alone).

Many wartime propaganda lies are preserved in this piece, including Nazi shrunken heads, and the Dachau homicidal gas chamber. In fact it seems that this was a finished documentary that had to have some of the narration cut out. As you watch this, never forget that the first thing to go in war, is the truth. 

The way in which the Allies blame all the wartime atrocities and responsibility for genocide squarely on the Axis, is beyond any measure of hypocrisy, nor words to describe. It is in fact human hypocrisy. The truth required no lies to describe.

 &quot; If a prisoner had a curiously-tattooed skin, it was taken from him, we can only hope he was dead when he was done. The skin was tanned, and made into lampshades, etc...these shrunken heads belonged to two Polish prisoners who had escaped, and been recaptured.&quot; ~ Alfred Hitchcock

